                        </extent>
                        <foliation>
                           <p>Foliated on every leaf in Persian in red ink and in English in pencil.
                           </p>
                        </foliation>
                        <collation>
                           <p>
                              <catchwords>Catchwords on the bottom-left corners of the verso.
                              </catchwords>
                           </p>
                        </collation>
                        <condition>
                           <p>Worm-eaten in a few pages. Detached from binding, with stitching
                              broken especially towards the end of the manuscript. </p>
                        </condition>
                     </supportDesc>
                     <layoutDesc>
                        <layout columns="0" ruledLines="13">
                           <p>13 lines per page. </p>
                        </layout>
                     </layoutDesc>
                  </objectDesc>
                  <handDesc>
                     <summary/>
                     <handNote>
                        <p>Indian nastaʻlīq tending to shikastah; copied in black ink, with headings
                           and overlinings in red. Copyist is <persName role="scr"
                              key="person_f2897">Muḥammad ʿAṭāʾ Allāh</persName> who may perhaps be
                           the same copyist as the scribe of Delhi Persian 57. </p>
                     </handNote>
                  </handDesc>
                  <additions>
                     <p>The flyleaf contains a note about one <persName>Raḥīm-dād Khān</persName>,
                        son of <persName>Nūr Muḥammad</persName>, resident of the middle of Multan,
                        and his full-brother <persName>Muḥammad Karīm</persName>, another person
                        with the name <persName>ʿAbd Allāh or ʿUbayd Allāh</persName>, someone named
                           <persName>Ghulām Nabī</persName> and children of a qāz̤ī. </p>
                     <p>Note on f. 1r giving the name of the work. </p>
                  </additions>
                  <bindingDesc>
                     <binding notBefore="1820" notAfter="1857">
                        <decoNote>Early binding of c. 1820.Outer binding leather with ruled yellow
                           rectangular frames; inside pastedown of marbled paper.</decoNote>
                     </binding>
                  </bindingDesc>
                  <sealDesc>
                     <seal subtype="rectangle" type="seal">
                        <p>Rectangular seal of former owner who can presumably be identitified with
                           the copyist: <persName role="fmo">Muḥammad ʻAṭā Allāh
                           Khān</persName>,1223 (1807/08) (f. 1r). </p>
                     </seal>
                     <seal subtype="oval" type="stamp">
                        <p>Black Government of India Delhi MSS oval stamp (ff. 1r, 259v). </p>
                     </seal>
                  </sealDesc>
